		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd like to ask for folks' opinion of having the PPU registers &quot;table-ised&quot;.  I recently saw this formatting being used in the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Frame_Counter" class="postlink">APU Frame Counter</a> page and found it a lot easier to understand/visualise, plus it's a bit more compact.<br /><br />Proposed new: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Koitsu#Controller_.28.242000.29_.3E_write">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User ... _.3E_write</a><!-- m --><br />Old: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User:Koitsu#Controller_.28.242000.29_.3E_write_2">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/User ... 3E_write_2</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I don't want to change anything unless the majority of folks like the change.  I can make this into a poll if that'd be preferred.

		

		</td>
