	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I personally prefer preformatted text. It copies and pastes easier and it's easier to edit. I'm not a fan of the lines drawn using pipes, plus signs, and dashes, but I find something like this both easier to read and easier to work with.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Bit&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Function<br />---&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;----------<br />0/1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Base nametable address <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (0 = $2000; 1 = $2400; 2 = $2800; 3 = $2C00)<br />2&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;VRAM address increment per CPU read/write of PPUDATA<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (0: add 1, going across; 1: add 32, going down)<br />3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sprite pattern table address for 8x8 sprites<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (0: $0000; 1: $1000; ignored in 8x16 mode)<br />4&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Background pattern table address (0: $0000; 1: $1000)<br />5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Sprite size (0: 8x8; 1: 8x16)<br />6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;PPU master/slave select<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (0: read backdrop from EXT pins; 1: output color on EXT pins)<br />7&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Generate an NMI at the start of the vertical blanking interval (0: off; 1: on)<br /></div><br />Or something like <a href="http://dl.dropbox.com/u/12027218/Shared%20Images/AutoDrop/autodrop411.png" class="postlink">this</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
