	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Wiki PPU register formatting</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Can I ask why you'd be copy-pasting stuff from the wiki to begin with?  This sounds like an edge use case for something uncommon.<br /><br />Also, bits are usually defined/documented in order of MSB to LSB (i.e. bit 7, bit 6, bit 5... bit 0).  That's a pretty much &quot;universal norm&quot; in technical documentation.  It all stems from most things being done left-to-right, and because of how &quot;bit math&quot; works (%00 = 0, %01 = 1, %10 = 2, %11 = 3, etc.) -- reversing that order isn't how computers work.  Maybe Hebrew documentation is different?  Dunno.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


